  "text": "Data collection and analysis are conducted iteratively. Initial data collection is followed by a review, in which we examine the materials to assess the quality of the data and to develop initial research questions. We also undertake preliminary analysis of a selected number of fragments and begin to reflect upon any particular actions and activities that might inform how we gather further data. The iterative design of data collection and analysis, therefore, allows us to progressively refine the analysis with regard to the practical issues and analytic insights that emerge through detailed inspection of the data [CITATION_1] .",
